      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver peak torque across a broad power band. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing M-Variable Differential Lock. The chassis has been inspected for subframe fatigue, with preventative reinforcement already completed to maintain torsional rigidity. Recent service includes a valve adjustment and cooling system overhaul. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains tight, and the suspension geometry is dialed for spirited driving. A true driver's specimen with all major mechanical hurdles addressed.",
